<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Several changes are also proposed to other related rules to implement the new criteria and to consolidate the general
gust requirements into a single section. Gust requirements are located in several different sections of part 25 that
pertain to continuous turbulence, lateral gusts, etc. This proposal would consolidate many of these gust requirements
into a revised &sect;25.341. In this regard, several changes to other sections are proposed to transfer requirements
and to revise references to these requirements. These include the relocation of &sect;25.305(d) to &sect;25.341(b)
and the transfer of &sect;&sect;25.331(a)(1) and 25.331(a)(2) to &sect;25.321 ``General'' and changing the title
of &sect;25.331 to ``Symmetric maneuvering conditions.'' Also the lateral gust requirements of &sect;25.351 would
be removed since the proposed &sect;25.341 addresses both vertical and lateral gusts. The gust envelope would no
longer be needed with the proposed criteria so it would be eliminated from &sect;25.333 and the title of this section
would be changed to ``Flight maneuvering envelope.'' 
